cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.NE 

This paper presents a new feature selection method that is suitable for both unsupervised and supervised problems. The paper extensively evaluates the proposed methods on many benchmark datasets, including large image-classification datasets (PASCAL VOC). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper proposes new ways of forming the feature adjacency matrix that perform better for unsupervised problems, which suggests the sub-categories cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as possible options.
